    • Method Detail

      • getOpString

        org.rioproject.opstring.OperationalString getOpString(java.lang.String type,
                                                      java.lang.String version,
                                                      java.lang.String name)
                                               throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Returns OperationalString object for given service.
        Parameters:
        type - Type of service. Required parameter.
        version - Version of service artifact. The default is the latest version.
        name - Tag of the service. If null, return random, matching type and version.
        Returns:
        Operational String as a String.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the service is configured to require version (the default) and version is not passed
        java.rmi.RemoteException
